# Date Validation Implementation Walkthrough

## Summary of Changes
After reviewing the system's architecture, we discovered that simple Orders (Pedidos de Comida) never ask for a manual date (they use standard automatic `auto_now_add=True`). However, the real issue lived inside the [ReservaForm](file:///c:/Users/Usuario/Downloads/restaurante/gestion/helpers/forms.py#99-149) where receptionist could create **Reservations (Reservas)** on dates prior to today's date. 

To fix this, we implemented strict date validation inside the `ReservaForm.clean()` method.

### Code Adjustments
- **Modified:** [c:\Users\Usuario\Downloads\restaurante\gestion\helpers\forms.py](file:///c:/Users/Usuario/Downloads/restaurante/gestion/helpers/forms.py)
  - Added a `datetime.date.today()` check.
  - Form validation now strictly enforces `fecha >= today`.
  - Added user-friendly interface error message block.
  
